branches let us work in isolation, it provide different working directory!
imagine branch as separate isolated workspace.
** when we switch between branches, our working directory will change **
branches are just some pointer that point to specific commit!

we develop on separate branch like "feature",
after testing and make sure it is stable,
we merge it to our main branch like "master"

our main branch like "master"
should always be stable, ready to release
and new joiner developer access to stable codes!

Note: git manage branching differently from other version control system!
      the other make a copy of all the project! it so heavy and expensive in big projects
      so they are very slow on branching! but git is supper fast!
      it does not make copy, it just create a simple pointer!

Note: branches are just 40 byte file that contain commit id.
      head is just file that contain branch-name.



